Dictionary

Dessert

Definition:

Sweet food eaten at the end of a meal.

Alimentos dulces que se comen al final de una comida.

Example:

For dessert there's apple pie or fruit.

De postre hay tarta de manzana o una pieza de fruta.

Spanish word:

Postre

Audio:

Fish and chips

Definition:

A typical English dish made of fried fish and fried potatoes.

Un plato típico inglés hecho de pescado frito y patatas fritas.

Example:

You can eat fish and chips in London.

Puedes comer pescado con patatas en Londres.

Spanish word:

Pescado con patatas

Audio:

Fizzy drink

Definition:

A cold drink full of gas bubbles with different flavours.

Una bebida fría con burbujas de diferentes sabores.

Example:

I like my fizzy drink very cold.

Me gusta mi refresco muy frío.

Spanish word:

Refresco

Audio:

Fortune cookie

Definition:

A Chinese cookie containing a paper with a proverb or prediction.

Una galleta china que contiene un papel con un proverbio o predicción.

Example:

My sister doesn’t like fortune cookies.

A mi hermana no le gustan las galletas de la fortuna.

Spanish word:

Galleta de la fortuna

Audio:

Hot-dog

Definition:

Sandwich with a sausage.

Bocadillo con una salchicha.

Example:

Can I have a hot dog?

¿Puedo comerme un perrito caliente?

Spanish word:

Perrito caliente

Audio:

Macaroni

Definition:

An Italian food, made of short thick tubes of pasta.

Una comida italiana hecha de tubos cortos de pasta.

Example:

I prefer macaroni and tomato.

Prefiero los macarrones con tomate.

Spanish word:

Macarrones

Audio:

Main

Definition:

The most important.

Principal, el más importante.

Example:

The main dish.

El plato principal.

Spanish word:

Principal (plato)

Audio:

Milkshake

Definition:

A cold drink made of milk, with some flavour, and ice cream sometimes.

Una bebida fría hecha de leche, algún sabor y a veces helado.

Example:

I prefer vanilla milkshake.

Prefiero el batido de vainilla.

Spanish word:

Batido

Audio:

Mince pie

Definition:

A pie filled with meat.

Un pastel relleno de carne.

Example:

We eat mince pie for Christmas.

Nosotros comemos pastel de carne en Navidad.

Spanish word:

Pastel de carne

Audio:

Noodles

Definition:

Like spaghetti but thinner.

Como los spaghettis pero más finos.

Example:

My dad loves noodles.

A mi papá le encantan los fideos.

Spanish word:

Fideos

Audio:

Pancake

Definition:

A flat, round, batter cake fried on both sides.

Un pastel redondo y aplastado de masa frita por ambos lados.

Example:

I prefer pancakes with chocolate and fruit.

Prefiero las tortitas con chocolate y fruta.

Spanish word:

Tortita

Audio:

Spring roll

Definition:

A Chinese pancake that is rolled up with vegetables or meat in it.

Un panqueque chino que se enrolla con verduras o carne.

Example:

We eat spring rolls every Monday.

Comemos rollos de primavera todos los lunes.

Spanish word:

Rollo de primavera

Audio:

Definition:

Appetizer.

Aperitivo.

Example:

I would like a salad as a starter.

Me gustaría una ensalada como entrante.

Entrante (plato)

Although more often used in formal testing situations MCQs can be used as a testing tool to stimulate thought and discussion on topics students may feel a little reticent in responding to. When designing a MCQ test consider the following:
  • What learning outcomes are the questions testing
  • What intellectual skills are being tested
  • What are the language skills of the audience
  • Gender and cultural issues
  • Avoid grammar language and question structures that might provide clues

When building an MCQ consider the following:
  • Use phrases that learners are familiar with and have encountered in their study
  • Keep responses concise
  • There should be some consistency between the stem and the responses
  • Provide enough options to challenge learners to think about their response
  • Try to make sure that correct responses are not more detailed than the distractors
  • Distractors should be incorrect but plausible

5. Grammar

Now you know something new about food.

You need to express your ideas correctly.

Here you can see how to do it.

Lectura facilitada

Read

You know something new about food.

Tú ya sabes algo nuevo sobre comida.

You need to express your ideas correctly.

Tú tienes que expresar tus ideas correctamente.

Here you can learn how to do it.

Aquí tú puedes aprender a hacerlo.

LUMEN dicen Do you need some help?

We are learning…

Do you like...?

INTERROGATIVE SENTENCES 

HOT DOGS

When we ask if you like a certain food, we use the plural nouns:

Do you like hot dogs?

TOMATOES

Do you like tomatoes?

FISH

The plural for fish is fish.

Do you like fish?

CAN

We use can to ask for food and to express a request.

Can I have some water, please?

Can I have some rice?

Can I have an orange juice?

CAN



Have (food) for (meal)

You can say what and when you eat this way:

Have (food) for (meal)

For example: I have cereal with milk for breakfast.

A SPANISH RECIPE
WRITE A SPANISH RECIPE

Now it is your turn to show how much you know about your country's cooking.

You have to work in PAIRS and write a SPANISH RECIPE using CANVA.
Text and Tasks

1. SEE THE VIDEO TO GET IDEAS FOR YOUR PROJECT.

2. SEARCH THE WEB FOR IDEAS.
You can use GOOGLE for example.

3. WRITE DOWN YOUR IDEAS IN YOUR PAPER.

4. USE CANVA EDUCATION(YOU HAVE INVITED THROUGH CLASSROOM)  TO CREATE A RECIPE FOR A SPANISH DISH.

5. PUBLISH YOUR RECIPE IN CLASSROOM.
